Reasoning: 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a new data structure for genomic databases.
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also likely as the paper discusses fast search in compressed genomic databases.
- cs.DB (Databases) is relevant as the paper deals with genomic databases and their compression.
- cs.CE (Computational Epidemiology) is a possible category as genomic databases are often used in epidemiological studies.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the efficiency of the proposed compressed self-index.
